Excessive CO2 production has meant that the ocean pH has dropped by 0.1 pH unit. Atmospheric CO2 is now 400 ppm CO2 but coral started dying on a big scale when CO2 reached 320 ppm, noting that atmospheric CO2 had not exceeded 280 ppm for lat 800,000 years until after the start of the Industrial Revolution (see “2011 climate change course”: https://sites.google.com/site/300orgsite/2011-climate-change-course ). 



